# UX Wave 1 — Token rewire + BLOCKER fixes — implementation plan

> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: use `gm` (this repo's execution coordinator — CLAUDE.md mandates it for non-trivial code changes). Each cycle below = one `gm` run (PLAN→EXECUTE→EMIT→VERIFY→COMPLETE) terminating in its own commit. Do NOT use subagent-driven-development or inline executing-plans — they bypass gm. Steps use `- [ ]` for tracking.

**Goal:** Upstream token-layer rewire + repair three `[BLOCKER]` UX bugs (#4 guest silent-discard, #17 analytics invisible select, #24 mobile no-egress) and adjacent HIGH findings (map-view chrome, creation dialog, state pills, focus ring).

**Architecture:** Semantic tokens become single source of theme truth. `[data-theme="dark"] { … }` at top level reassigns the semantic tokens; components consume tokens only. Eleven override blocks deleted AFTER their base rules are rewritten to consume tokens. Three blocker bugs repaired with defense-in-depth invariant: failed extraction never mutates `contentStore`, in-memory `concepts`, or localStorage `concepts`, regardless of UI state.

**Terminology correction (from review):** `setState(newState)` in `app.js:1265` is the concept-shell state mutator (`growing` / `fractured` / `hibernating` / `actualized`) — NOT a view router. View routing uses `showDashboard()` / `showLibrary()` / `showAnalytics()` / `showSettings()`. CLAUDE.md invariant #1 covers setState() for *control-state*, which is concept-level. Map-view exit uses the existing view-router functions.

**Cache-busting (from review):** `public/styles.css` imports per-file `?v=NN` query versions. Every CSS edit in a cycle must bump the touched file's `?v=` in `public/styles.css`. `public/index.html:25` also carries `styles.css?v=12` — bump whenever `public/styles.css` content changes.

**Sanitization contract (from review):** `recordExtractRun({ reason: … })` rows are rendered to user-visible analytics via `browser-analytics.js:326` (`row.reason || …`). Therefore raw `err.message` must NOT go into `reason`. Sanitized copy in `reason`; raw detail in `reason_raw` (never rendered) or console only.

**Tech Stack:** Vanilla JS/HTML/CSS only (CLAUDE.md). No build step. `gm` state-machine coordinates execution. Browser manual verify is the verification surface (0 unit tests exist in repo).

**Spec:** `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-18-ux-wave1-token-rewire-design.prd`
**Canonical tokens:** `/tmp/design-ndrpUZ/socratink-design-system/project/colors_and_type.css`
**Branch:** `worktree-ux-wave1-token-rewire`

