- [ ] **Step 5: Add global `:focus-visible` rule to `public/css/base.css`**

At end of file, append:

```css
/* ============================================================
   Focus ring — a11y.
   Every interactive element inherits this. No browser-default blue.
   --accent-ring token reassigns in dark mode.
   ============================================================ */
:focus-visible {
  outline: none;
  box-shadow: var(--accent-ring);
  border-radius: 4px;
}

/* Form-controls need explicit ring — some browsers strip it from input/select */
input:focus-visible,
textarea:focus-visible,
select:focus-visible,
button:focus-visible,
a:focus-visible,
[role="button"]:focus-visible {
  outline: none;
  box-shadow: var(--accent-ring);
}

/* Reduced-motion: pin short transitions to 0ms on user request */
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  *,
  *::before,
  *::after {
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    animation-iteration-count: 1 !important;
  }
}
```

