- [ ] **Step 3: Wire analytics page pill rendering to state variants**

In `public/js/learner-analytics.js` or wherever pills render, search for class string `analytics-pill` or similar. Add a class-suffix map by state:

```javascript
// Map state to pill variant class. Defensive default keeps current lavender.
function analyticsPillClass(state) {
  switch (state) {
    case 'solidified': return 'pill pill--solid';
    case 'primed':     return 'pill pill--primed';
    case 'drilled':    return 'pill pill--drilled';
    case 'locked':     return 'pill pill--locked';
    case 'misconception':
    case 'fractured':  return 'pill pill--danger';
    default:           return 'pill';
  }
}
```

Apply the helper where analytics tiles render their state pill. (Exact line range requires reading `public/js/learner-analytics.js` — estimated 200-400L; grep for `pill` there first.)

