## Cycle C3 — Override-block audit + crystal dark block move

**Goal:** Delete 11 redundant `[data-theme="dark"]` blocks — but only AFTER rewriting their base rules to consume tokens. Base rules currently hardcode light-theme gradients (e.g., `ai-runs-dashboard.css:27` uses `rgba(--white-rgb, 0.9) → rgba(--cream-50-rgb, 0.82)`). Deleting the dark override without first rewriting the base leaves analytics surfaces cream in dark mode.

Move 65-line token reassignment block from `crystal.css` to `variables.css` (already there from C1; C3 deletes the duplicate). Keep 5 component-specific blocks.

**Ordering discipline: rewrite base rule → verify in both themes → delete dark override → verify again.** Per-rule, not batched.

### C3 Files

- **Modify** `public/css/crystal.css` (delete lines 174-238 — dark-token block)
- **Modify** `public/css/components.css` (delete `body[data-theme="dark"] .auth-link` at L145-149)
- **Modify** `public/css/layout.css` (delete L147 hero-card, L149-151 settings-page-card, L153 `#card` blocks)
- **Modify** `public/css/ai-runs-dashboard.css` (delete L564-570 analytics-header/panel/status/metric-card/tip-card block)

### C3 Steps

- [ ] **Step 1: Delete duplicate token block from `crystal.css`**

Delete lines 172-238 (the `/* ── 6. Night mode ──... */` section through closing `}` of the `[data-theme="dark"]` block). These tokens now live in `variables.css` from C1.

**Keep** lines 92-121 (`.tile-group.empty`, `.tile-group.selected`, `#grid-container::before` tile geometry overrides) — these are NOT token reassignments, they're specific hex values for tile rendering not covered by tokens.

- [ ] **Step 2: Delete `body[data-theme="dark"] .auth-link` from `components.css`**

Delete lines 145-149 (entire block). `.auth-link` uses `--accent-primary` which flips automatically via tokens.

- [ ] **Step 3: Audit layout.css base rules for hero-card / settings-page-card / #card before deleting dark blocks**

For each of the three selectors, read the base rule (search in `layout.css` for `.hero-card {`, `.settings-page-card {`, `#card {`). Confirm base already uses `--surface-card` / `--card-bg` / `--surface-page` etc. — if base is token-derivable, delete dark block; if hardcoded, rewrite base first.

Expected disposition:
- `.hero-card` base at `layout.css:99` uses `background: var(--surface-card);` (token-derivable). **Delete L147 dark override.**
- `.settings-page-card` — if base uses `linear-gradient(180deg, var(--gradient-card-start), var(--gradient-card-end))` already, dark block is literally identical → **delete L149-151**. If base is different, **make base use those tokens first**, then delete.
