## Cycle C5 — Map-view chrome (← Dashboard text-back)

**Goal:** Map view has one unambiguous back control. `<` drawer-toggle no longer appears in map view; `×` close button removed. Single `← Dashboard` text link.

**Critical correction from review:** `setState(newState)` at `app.js:1265` is the **concept-shell state mutator** (`growing`/`fractured`/`hibernating`/`actualized`) — NOT a view router. Passing an object like `{ view: 'dashboard' }` would corrupt concept state. View routing is handled by `showDashboard()` (already exposed on `window.App`, called from existing nav links at `index.html:74` and `public/index.html:47`). Map-view exit calls `showDashboard()`, which handles the route transition and tears down map state.

