---

## Post-cycle — rerun baseline browser QA prompt

After C6 commits, rerun the 16-check baseline browser QA prompt from the brainstorming transcript. All 16 must pass. Any failure → triage: pre-existing issue, regression from a specific cycle (revert that cycle alone), or spec gap (file new Wave 2 item).

## Rollback

Each cycle = one commit. Bad cycle in isolation → `git revert <sha>`.

**Important:** reverting C1 alone does NOT unwind downstream — C2–C6 depend on tokens C1 introduced (`--node-*`, `--node-*-rgb`, dark-block reassignment). Reverting C1 while C2–C6 are landed leaves a broken build. To undo C1 after downstream cycles, revert the range (`git revert C6..C1` or equivalent) or squash-revert via a compensating commit.

Safest: verify each cycle in browser before the next begins. If C1 fails verify, revert immediately before starting C2.

## Self-review checklist (for executing agent)

- Each cycle lands as one commit, per-file `?v=` versions bumped in `public/styles.css` and `styles.css?v=` in `public/index.html`.
- Cycle commit message references the UX-todo item(s) resolved.
- Invariants preserved: `setState()` concept-shell mutator untouched (not used for view routing), knowledge-map drill-state source of truth, `contentStore` volatile, Gemini SDK untouched, auth routes untouched.
- View routing uses `showDashboard()` / `showLibrary()` / etc., NOT `setState(...)`.
- Guest detection uses `session.guest_mode`, NOT `session.is_guest`.
- Dialog `inert` applied to body-children siblings (no `#app-root` exists), cleared exactly on close.
- Banner inserted into `dialog.bannerSlot`, NOT prepended into `buildContentInputUI` container (which would be wiped by its own `innerHTML =`).
- `recordExtractRun` `reason` field populated with **sanitized** copy only (it is rendered to user-visible analytics via `browser-analytics.js:326`); raw detail goes to console and, if schema allows, a never-rendered `reason_raw` field.
- No new consumers of `--bg` / `--card-bg` / `--text` / `--primary` aliases introduced in new code written this wave.
- Pill CSS uses `--node-*-rgb` channel tokens, not hardcoded hex.
- Analytics base rules (and any other base rule behind a deleted dark override) were rewritten to consume tokens BEFORE the dark override was deleted — per-selector, verified in both themes.
- Guard is on extraction-success path (`isValidKnowledgeMap`), not submit-gate — dev tools cannot bypass it by re-enabling disabled inputs.
- Python tests run post-C6: `pytest tests/test_auth_gate.py tests/test_auth_router.py tests/test_url_import.py -v` — all pass.
